assume p in V;
then consider r being  real number such that A6: r > ( 0 ) and A7: ( Ball (p1,r) ) c= V by TOPMETR:15;
A8: ( f .: ( Ball (p1,r) ) ) c= ( f .: V ) by A7,RELAT_1:123;
(ex s being  positive  real number st ( Ball (q,s) ) c= ( f .: ( Ball (p1,r) ) )) by A4,A5,A6;
hence thesis by A8,XBOOLE_1:1;
end;
hence thesis by CKB4:1;
